article.description: Trey Freeman scored 34 of his career-high 42 in the second half to set the Conference USA tournament record for points in a game and help No. 5 seed Old Dominion beat Western Kentucky 89-77 Frida
article.headline: Freeman's record 42 points leads ODU past WKU in C-USA
article.linkText: Freeman's record 42 points leads ODU past WKU in C-USA
article.story: BIRMINGHAM, Ala. -- Trey Freeman scored 34 of his career-high 42 in the second half to set the Conference USA tournament record for points in a game and help No. 5 seed Old Dominion beat Western Kentucky 89-77 Friday and advance to the championship game. Old Dominion (22-12), which has won seven games in a row and 12 of its last 14, will face No. 2 seed Middle Tennessee (23-9) for the title Saturday. Freeman made 15 of 25 from the field, including 4 of 4 from 3-point range, and all of his eight free throws. Aaron Bacote added 18 points and Brandan Stith scored 14, on 4-of-5 shooting, with 13 rebounds. Aaron Cosby led Western Kentucky (18-16) with 21 points. Nigel Snipes added 18, all on a career-best six 3s. The Hilltoppers led 35-32 at halftime, but ODU shot 65.4 percent (17 of 26) -- its season high for a half this season -- and outrebounded WKU 21-12 after halftime.
